{"title_page": "List of Deakin University people", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=November 2018}}\nThis is a '''list of [[Deakin University]] people''', including notable alumni and staff.\n\n==Notable alumni==\n\n===Business===\n* [[Simon Garlick]], CEO of the Western Bulldogs: BExSc\n* Carolyn Hardy, CEO UNICEF Australia: BA, MA<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deakin.edu.au/current-students/study-information/graduation/past-ceremonies/2007/23oct11am07bcer.php?feedback=true|title=Graduation|publisher=|accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Christopher Lynch (businessman)|Christopher Lynch]], former Chief Financial Officer & Former Director of [[BHP Billiton]], CEO of [[Transurban]] Ltd: [[BCom]], [[MBA]]\n* [[Michael Malouf]], former Chief Executive Officer, [[Carlton Football Club]]: MBA\n* [[Lindsay Maxsted]], Chairman [[Westpac Banking Corporation]]\n* [[Jim Stynes]] OAM, businessman and Chairman of [[Melbourne Football Club]]: BEd\n* [[Diana Taylor (businesswoman)|Diana Taylor]] Prominent Businesswoman\n\n===Government===\n====Politicians====\n\n=====Federal politicians=====\n* [[Mark Butler]] MP, Federal Member for Port Adelaide\n* [[Trish Crossin]], [[Australian Senate|Senator]] for [[Northern Territory]]\n* [[Bridget McKenzie]], Senator for Victoria, Deputy Leader of the Nationals\n\n=====Australian state and territory politicians=====\n* [[Julie Attwood]],  Member of [[Legislative Assembly of Queensland]]\n* [[John Brumby]], former Premier and Treasurer of the State of [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]: Dip Ed\n* [[Denis Napthine]], Premier of the State of [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]: MBA\n\n=====International politicians=====\n*  [[Mahmoud Saikal]], Permanent representative of Afghanistan to the UN [https://afghanistan-un.org/permanent-representative/biography/]\n\n====Public servants====\n* [[Neil Comrie]], former Chief Commissioner of [[Victoria Police]]: BA (Police Studies)\n\n===Humanities===\n====Arts====\n* [[Anurag Singh (director)|Anurag Singh]](director), one of the best Pollywood and Bollywood director \n*[[Rodger Corser]], Australian actor: Honours B.A in Media Studies\n* Tony Ellwood, Director of the [[National Gallery of Victoria]] and former director of [[Queensland Art Gallery]] and [[Gallery of Modern Art, Glasgow|Gallery of Modern Art]]: M.App.Sc.(Museum Studies)<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/arts/ellwood-to-bet-on-blockbuster-success/story-e6frg8n6-1226285523237 |title=National Gallery of Victoria appointment|accessdate=2012-03-02 | first=Michaela |last=Boland |date=1 March 2012 |work=The Australian}}</ref>\n* [[Oliver Feltham]], contemporary philosopher and English translator of [[Alain Badiou]]'s ''Being and Event'' (2006)\n* [[Mandawuy Yunupingu]], indigenous musician, community leader and  [http://www.australianoftheyear.org.au/honour-roll/?view=landing&year=1992 Australian of the Year (1992)]: BA\n* [[Nitya Prakash]], Bestselling Author\n\n====Journalism====\n* [[Emma Alberici]], journalist/presenter with the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]]\n* [[Livinia Nixon]], [[Nine Network]] weather presenter: BCom, BA\n* [[Leigh Sales]], [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]] journalist, anchor of [[Lateline]] and book writer: Master of International Relations, Brisbane Writers Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bwf.org.au/|title=Brisbane Writers Festival|author=Studio None|publisher=|accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Stella Young]], comedian, journalist and disability rights activist: BA\n* [[Nathan Templeton (journalist)|Nathan Templeton]], former ''[[10 News First]]'' sports reporter and now the Melbourne correspondent on ''[[Sunrise (Australian TV program)|Sunrise]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/nathan-templeton-85bb868a/|title=Nathan Templeton|publisher=[[LinkedIn]]|accessdate=17 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Sport===\n* [[Jimmy Bartel]], 2007 [[Brownlow Medal]]list and triple [[Australian Football League|AFL]] Premiership Player in 2007, 2009 and 2011 with the [[Geelong Football Club]]. 2011 [[Norm Smith]] medallist\n* [[Mark Blake (Australian rules footballer)|Mark Blake]], 2009 [[Australian Football League|AFL]] Premiership player with the [[Geelong Football Club]]\n* [[Campbell Brown (footballer)|Campbell Brown]], 2008 [[Australian Football League|AFL]] Premiership player with [[Hawthorn Football Club]] and inaugural [[Gold Coast Football Club]] player: BCom (Sports Management)\n* [[Tim Callan]], [[Australian Football League|AFL]] footballer with the [[Western Bulldogs]]: BCom\n* [[Briony Cole]], Gold medalist, [[2006 Commonwealth Games]], & Silver medalist, [[2008 Beijing Olympics]]\n* [[Peter Daniel (Australian footballer)|Peter Daniel]], former footballer for Essendon Football Club, AFL: DipTeach\n* [[Ben Graham (footballer)|Ben Graham]], former [[Geelong Football Club]] star, now a [[Punter (football)|punter]] for the [[Arizona Cardinals]] of the [[National Football League]]; first Australian to play in the [[Super Bowl]]: BCom\n* [[Tom Harley]], Dual Premiership Captain of [[Geelong Football Club]] in 2007 and 2009: BCom\n* [[Geoff Hunt]], World Champion squash player: Charles William apeGrad Dip (Nutrition)\n* [[Michael Klinger]], Australian cricketer<ref>{{cite web|last1=Greig|first1=Fiona|title=Star cricketer and Deakin student Michael Klinger shares his amazing story|url=https://blogs.deakin.edu.au/deakinlife/2016/05/04/star-cricketer-and-deakin-student-michael-klinger-shares-his-amazing-story/|publisher=Deakin University|accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Carmen Marton]], Australia's first ever world taekwondo champion\n* [[Mat McBriar]], [[Punter (football)|punter]] for the [[Dallas Cowboys]] of the [[National Football League]]\n* [[Henry Playfair]], [[Australian Football League|AFL]] footballer with the [[Sydney Swans]]: BCom\n* [[Jeff Rowley]], surfer and celebrity ppeaker: [[MBA]] in leadership and communications.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jeffrowley.com/|title=Jeff Rowley \u2013 Big Wave Surfer|publisher=|accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Matt Stevic]], AFL umpire<ref>{{cite web|title=Best on ground \u2013 AFL Grand Final, 2012|url=https://blogs.deakin.edu.au/deakinlife/2012/09/28/best-on-ground-afl-grand-final-2012-2/|website=Deakin Life|publisher=Deakin University|accessdate=16 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Other===\n* [[Phillip Aspinall]], [[Primate (bishop)|Primate]] of the [[Anglican Church]] in Australia: MBA\n* Colonel [[Benito T. de Leon]], Military Officer, Philippines Army: MA (Strategic Studies)\n* [[Mark Kelly (general)|Major General Mark Kelly]], Officer of the [[Australian Army]]: Grad.Dip. Defence Studies\n* [[James Kilgore]], as Charles William Pape, member of the [[Symbionese Liberation Army]]: PhD<ref>{{cite web|title=Century of 'servants' : domestic workers in Zimbabwe 1890-1990|url=http://dro.deakin.edu.au/view/DU:30027575|website=Deakin University|accessdate=6 March 2017|date=1992}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2003/jan/26/features.magazine57 | location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Gavin | last=Evans | title=A life on the run | date=26 January 2003}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Vivian Lucas Jones]], Bishop of the Anglican Church in Australia\n* Kathryn Sheffield, remote sensing, BS\n\n\n==Notable staff==\n*[[Kevin Anderson (cinematographer)|Kevin Anderson]], filmmaker\n*[[Kate Buchanan]] ARC Future Fellow\n*Tania de Koning-Ward,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deakin.edu.au/research/stories/2011/06/13/top-award-to-dr-tania-de-koning-ward|title=Top award to Dr Tania de Koning-Ward|author=Deputy Vice Chancellor (Research) Office|date=13 June 2011|publisher=|accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref> Commonwealth Health Minister's Medal for Excellence in Health and Medical Research\n*Peter Hodgson,<ref>[http://www.arc.gov.au/pdf/FL09_Biographies.pdf Hodgson's Honour] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141005122735/http://www.arc.gov.au/pdf/FL09_Biographies.pdf |date=5 October 2014 }}</ref> 2009 Australian Laureate Fellow\n*[[John Jonas]], Birks Professor of Metallurgy, [[McGill University]]: Visiting Professor.\n*[[Ross Oakley]], former [[Australian Football League]] CEO: Adjunct Professor in the Faculty of Business and Law\n*[[David Parkin]], former coach of [[Carlton Football Club|Carlton]] and [[Hawthorn Football Club]]s: Lecturer in Exercise Science.\n*[[Mark Weinberg (judge)|Mark Weinberg]], Chief Justice of Norfolk Island: Adjunct Professor, School of Law.\n*[[Jim Kennan]], former politician, Adjunct Professor of Law\n*[[Svetha Venkatesh]], Director of the Centre for Pattern Recognition and Data Analytics\n\n==Administration==\n\n=== Chancellors ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#fc3;\"\n! Order !! [[Chancellor (education)|Chancellor]]  !! Years !! Notes\n|-\n| 1 || John Stanhope AM || 2016\u2014present ||\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Vice-Chancellors ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#fc3;\"\n! Order !! [[Vice-Chancellor]] !! Years !! Notes\n|-\n| 1  || [[Frederic Jevons]]|| 1977\u20131985 || \n|-\n| 2  || [[Malcolm Skilbeck]] || 1986\u20131991 || \n|-\n| 3  || [[John A. Hay]] || 1992\u20131996 || \n|-\n| 4  || [[Geoff Wilson (professor)|Geoff Wilson]] || 1997\u20132002 || \n|-\n| 5  || [[Sally Walker]] || 2003\u20132010 ||\n|-\n| 6  || [[Jane den Hollander]] || 2010\u2013present ||\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Education in Geelong]]\n[[Category:Universities in Victoria (Australia)]]\n[[Category:Universities in Melbourne]]\n[[Category:Deakin University|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=November 2018}}\nThis is a '''list of [[Deakin University]] people''', including notable alumni and staff.\n\n==Notable alumni==\n\n===Business===\n* [[Simon Garlick]], CEO of the Western Bulldogs: BExSc\n* Carolyn Hardy, CEO UNICEF Australia: BA, MA<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deakin.edu.au/current-students