{"title_page": "Breathe (Australian band)", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Breathe\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = breathe.\n| origin          = [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Soul music|Soul]]\n* [[Electronic music|electronic]]\n* [[Minimal music|minimal]]\n}}\n| years_active    = \n| label           = {{flatlist|\n* Silk\n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Movement (band)|Movement]]\n* [[Illangelo]]\n}}\n| website         = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n| current_members = \n* Sean Walker\n* Andrew Grant\n| past_members    = \n}}\n\n'''Breathe''' (stylised as '''breathe.''') is an Australian [[Minimal music|minimal]] soul duo that blends [[Soul music|soul]] and [[Electronic music|electronic]] music. They consist of Sean Walker (a founding member of the band [[Movement (band)|Movement]]) and Andrew Grant. They are currently based in [[Sydney]], [[Australia]]<ref name=\"recstudios\">{{cite web|url=http://beta.recstudios.com.au/|website=beta.recstudios.com.au|title=REC Studios|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"recstudios2\">{{cite web|url=http://beta.recstudios.com.au/2015/06/11/george-maple/|title=George Maple|website=REC Studios|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"XLR8R\">{{cite web |url=https://xlr8r.com/mp3/breathe-are-you-all-good/ |title=Breathe \"Are You All Good?\" |last= |first= |date= |work=XLR8R |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and [[Toronto]], [[Canada]].<ref name=\"Clash\"/>\n\n==History==\nBreathe was formed in [[Sydney]] in 2018. The band was founded by Sean Walker, who had founded the Australian \"[[Minimal music|minimal]] soul\" band [[Movement (band)|Movement]],<ref name=\"cmenesguen\">{{cite web | first = Clemence | last = Menesguen | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150702132650/http://www.konbini.com/en/entertainment-2/konbini-meets-movement/ | url = http://www.konbini.com/en/music/konbini-meets-movement/ | title = ''Konbini'' Meets New Aussie Band Movement | work = Konbini | archivedate = 2015-07-02 | date = July 2014 | accessdate = 2018-08-06 }}</ref> and Andrew Grant.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fbiradio.com/independent-artist-of-the-week-the-tapes/ |title=Independent Artist Of The Week: The Tapes |last=Rae |first=Tanya Bonnie |date= |work= |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref>\n\nTheir debut single ''Are You All Good'' was released in September 2018 via the label Silk,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.purplesneakers.com.au/2018/09/watch-breathe-are-you-all-good/ |title=Introducing the bruised late-night soul of breathe. with \u2018Are You All Good?\u2019 |last= |first= |date= |work=Purple Sneakers |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.twntythree.com/introducing-breathe-listen-to-their-debut-single-are-you-all-good/ |title=Introducing breathe. listen to their debut single \u2018Are you all good?\u2019 |last= |first= |date=September 13, 2018 |work=twnty three |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and was described as \"late night emotion.\"<ref name=\"XLR8R\" /> It was also released with a self-directed music video in collaboration with cinematographer Tim Nagle.<ref name=\"timnagle\">{{cite web|url=https://www.timnagle.com/music-videos/|title=Music Videos &#124; Tim Jude Nagle |website=timnagle.com|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"imdb\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6749497/|title=Tim Nagle|website=IMDb|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref>\n\nBreathe's second single ''London''<ref name=\"Line\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/new-music/discovery/breathe-london|title=Sydney duo breathe. project ghostly comfort on atmospheric new cut \"London\" |last=Kenneally |first=Cerys |date=22 February 2019 |work=The Line of Best Fit |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> was premiered by ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/02/premiere-breathe-london |title=Premiere: Australian Duo Breathe. Take Us On A Chillingly Soulful Trip Round \"London\" On New Single |last=Keith |first=James |date=Feb 21, 2019 |work=Complex |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and The Line of Best Fit has compared the music to \"the beauty of a peaceful night.\"<ref name=\"Line\" />\n\nTheir third single, ''Haze'', was released in 2019.<ref name=\"Clash\">{{cite web |url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/australian-production-duo-breathe-drop-new-single-haze |title=Australian Production Duo Breathe. Drop New Single 'Haze' |last=Murray |first=Robin |date=Sep 27, 2019 |work=Clash |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"Hypebeast\">{{cite web |url=https://hypebeast.com/2019/9/breathe-haze-stream-music-video |title=breathe. Drops Atmospheric New Single \"Haze.\" |last=Caraan |first=Sophie |date=Sep 28, 2019 |work=Hypebeast |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> The music video for ''Haze'' was directed by Dave May of Tall Story Films.<ref name=\"Hypebeast\"/>\n\nBreathe's music was described as \"[[Minimal music|minimal]] soul\" as well as \"late night soul\"<ref name=\"XLR8R\" /> that is \"brilliantly [[Minimal music|minimalistic]].\"<ref name=\"coveragebook\">{{cite web|url=https://coveragebook.com/b/6b7820f1|website=coveragebook.com|title=Breathe - press coverage |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> [[Rufus du Sol]] described the music as a \"sultry underworld that pulls you right in\", and [[Ta-ku]] said the band's music \"hit me right in my feelings.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pilerats.com/music/electronic/introducing-breathe-are-you-all-good/ |title=Meet Aus super-duo breathe and their incredible debut single, Are You All Good? |last=Hayden |first=Davies |date=2018 |work=Pilerats |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref>\n\nIndie Shuffle has compared the band to [[Moses Sumney]] and [[Michael Kiwanuka]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indieshuffle.com/breathe-are-you-all-good/|title=breathe. - Are You All Good?  |date=2018 |work=Indie Shuffle |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and Hypebeast reviewed ''Haze'' as an \"atmospheric\" song that gives off a \"ghostly yet lovesick vibe.\"<ref name=\"Hypebeast\"/>\n\n== Members ==\n* Sean Walker&nbsp;\u2013 percussion, guitar, production, mixing <small>(2018\u2013present)</small>\n* Andrew Grant&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar, synthesizers, production, mixing <small>(2018\u2013present)</small>\n\n== Discography ==\n;Singles\n* ''Are You All Good?'' (2018)\n* ''London'' (2019)\n* ''Haze'' (2019)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Movement (band)]]\n* [[Illangelo]]\n* [[Minimal music]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|1}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[:Category:Australian electronic music groups]]\n[[:Category:Australian soul musical groups]]\n[[:Category:2018 establishments in Australia]]\n[[:Category:Musical groups established in 2018]]\n[[:Category:Musical groups from Sydney]]\n[[:Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Australia-musician-stub}}\n{{Uncategorized stub|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Breathe\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = breathe.\n| origin          = [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Soul music|Soul]]\n* [[Electronic music|electronic]]\n* [[Minimal music|minimal]]\n}}\n| years_active    = \n| label           = {{flatlist|\n* Silk\n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Movement (band)|Movement]]\n* [[Illangelo]]\n}}\n| website         = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n| current_members = \n* Sean Walker\n* Andrew Grant\n| past_members    = \n}}\n\n'''Breathe''' (stylised as '''breathe.''') is an Australian [[Minimal music|minimal]] soul duo that blends [[Soul music|soul]] and [[Electronic music|electronic]] music. They consist of Sean Walker (a founding member of the band [[Movement (band)|Movement]]) and Andrew Grant. They are currently based in [[Sydney]], [[Australia]]<ref name=\"recstudios\">{{cite web|url=http://beta.recstudios.com.au/|website=beta.recstudios.com.au|title=REC Studios|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"recstudios2\">{{cite web|url=http://beta.recstudios.com.au/2015/06/11/george-maple/|title=George Maple|website=REC Studios|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"XLR8R\">{{cite web |url=https://xlr8r.com/mp3/breathe-are-you-all-good/ |title=Breathe \"Are You All Good?\" |last= |first= |date= |work=XLR8R |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and [[Toronto]], [[Canada]].<ref name=\"Clash\"/>\n\n==History==\nBreathe was formed in [[Sydney]] in 2018. The band was founded by Sean Walker, who had founded the Australian \"[[Minimal music|minimal]] soul\" band [[Movement (band)|Movement]],<ref name=\"cmenesguen\">{{cite web | first = Clemence | last = Menesguen | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150702132650/http://www.konbini.com/en/entertainment-2/konbini-meets-movement/ | url = http://www.konbini.com/en/music/konbini-meets-movement/ | title = ''Konbini'' Meets New Aussie Band Movement | work = Konbini | archivedate = 2015-07-02 | date = July 2014 | accessdate = 2018-08-06 }}</ref> and Andrew Grant.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fbiradio.com/independent-artist-of-the-week-the-tapes/ |title=Independent Artist Of The Week: The Tapes |last=Rae |first=Tanya Bonnie |date= |work= |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref>\n\nTheir debut single ''Are You All Good'' was released in September 2018 via the label Silk,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.purplesneakers.com.au/2018/09/watch-breathe-are-you-all-good/ |title=Introducing the bruised late-night soul of breathe. with \u2018Are You All Good?\u2019 |last= |first= |date= |work=Purple Sneakers |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.twntythree.com/introducing-breathe-listen-to-their-debut-single-are-you-all-good/ |title=Introducing breathe. listen to their debut single \u2018Are you all good?\u2019 |last= |first= |date=September 13, 2018 |work=twnty three |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and was described as \"late night emotion.\"<ref name=\"XLR8R\" /> It was also released with a self-directed music video in collaboration with cinematographer Tim Nagle.<ref name=\"timnagle\">{{cite web|url=https://www.timnagle.com/music-videos/|title=Music Videos &#124; Tim Jude Nagle |website=timnagle.com|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"imdb\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6749497/|title=Tim Nagle|website=IMDb|accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref>\n\nBreathe's second single ''London''<ref name=\"Line\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/new-music/discovery/breathe-london|title=Sydney duo breathe. project ghostly comfort on atmospheric new cut \"London\" |last=Kenneally |first=Cerys |date=22 February 2019 |work=The Line of Best Fit |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> was premiered by ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/02/premiere-breathe-london |title=Premiere: Australian Duo Breathe. Take Us On A Chillingly Soulful Trip Round \"London\" On New Single |last=Keith |first=James |date=Feb 21, 2019 |work=Complex |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and The Line of Best Fit has compared the music to \"the beauty of a peaceful night.\"<ref name=\"Line\" />\n\nTheir third single, ''Haze'', was released in 2019.<ref name=\"Clash\">{{cite web |url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/australian-production-duo-breathe-drop-new-single-haze |title=Australian Production Duo Breathe. Drop New Single 'Haze' |last=Murray |first=Robin |date=Sep 27, 2019 |work=Clash |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref><ref name=\"Hypebeast\">{{cite web |url=https://hypebeast.com/2019/9/breathe-haze-stream-music-video |title=breathe. Drops Atmospheric New Single \"Haze.\" |last=Caraan |first=Sophie |date=Sep 28, 2019 |work=Hypebeast |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> The music video for ''Haze'' was directed by Dave May of Tall Story Films.<ref name=\"Hypebeast\"/>\n\nBreathe's music was described as \"[[Minimal music|minimal]] soul\" as well as \"late night soul\"<ref name=\"XLR8R\" /> that is \"brilliantly [[Minimal music|minimalistic]].\"<ref name=\"coveragebook\">{{cite web|url=https://coveragebook.com/b/6b7820f1|website=coveragebook.com|title=Breathe - press coverage |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> [[Rufus du Sol]] described the music as a \"sultry underworld that pulls you right in\", and [[Ta-ku]] said the band's music \"hit me right in my feelings.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pilerats.com/music/electronic/introducing-breathe-are-you-all-good/ |title=Meet Aus super-duo breathe and their incredible debut single, Are You All Good? |last=Hayden |first=Davies |date=2018 |work=Pilerats |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref>\n\nIndie Shuffle has compared the band to [[Moses Sumney]] and [[Michael Kiwanuka]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indieshuffle.com/breathe-are-you-all-good/|title=breathe. - Are You All Good?  |date=2018 |work=Indie Shuffle |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> and Hypebeast reviewed ''Haze'' as an \"atmospheric\" song that gives off a \"ghostly yet lovesick vibe.\"<ref name=\"Hypebeast\"/>\n\n== Members ==\n* Sean Walker&nbsp;\u2013 percussion, guitar, production, mixing <small>(2018\u2013present)</small>\n* Andrew Grant&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar, synthesizers, production, mixing <small>(2018\u2013present)</small>\n\n== Discography ==\n;Singles\n* ''Are You All Good?'' (2018)\n* ''London'' (2019)\n* ''Haze'' (2019)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Movement (band)]]\n* [[Illangelo]]\n* [[Minimal music]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|1}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[:Category:Australian electronic music groups]]\n[[:Category:Australian soul musical groups]]\n[[:Category:2018 establishments in Australia]]\n[[:Category:Musical groups established in 2018]]\n[[:Category:Musical groups from Sydney]]\n[[:Category:Living people]]\n\n{{Australia-musician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up, addeduncategorisedtag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breathe_(Australian_band)"}
{"title_page": "1979 Toronto International Film Festival", "text_new": "{{Infobox film festival\n| name           = 1979 Toronto International Film Festival\n| image          = 1979 Toronto International Film Festival poster.jpg\n| caption        = Festival poster\n| host           = Toronto International Film Festival Group\n| number         = \n| opening        = \n| closing        = \n| location       = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]\n| language       = English\n| date           = {{Start date|1979|09|06}}\u2013{{End date|1979|09|15}}\n| website        = {{URL|tiff.net}}\n}}\nThe 4th '''[[Toronto International Film Festival]]''' ('''TIFF''') took place in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada between September 6 and September 15, 1979. This year ''The American Nightmare'' retrospective on [[Horror film|American horror films]] was organized by Canadian critic [[Robin Wood (critic)|Robin Wood]] and Richard Lippe.<ref name=\"a\">{{cite web|url=http://tiff.net/about/tiffhistory|title=TIFF History|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015055839/http://tiff.net/about/tiffhistory|archive-date=2013-10-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Brian De Palma]] and [[George A. Romero]] attended the retrospective as guests.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thetfs.ca/2012/09/04/a-brief-history-of-tiff/|title=A brief history of TIFF|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014145209/http://thetfs.ca/2012/09/04/a-brief-history-of-tiff/|archive-date=October 14, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jam.canoe.ca/Movies/Film_Festivals/Toronto/2009/about/|title=Taking a look back at TIFF|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20131012155556/http://jam.canoe.ca/Movies/Film_Festivals/Toronto/2009/about/|archive-date=2013-10-12|url-status=dead}}</ref> Also this year ''Industry programme trade forum'' was started by festival, which continued till 1991.<ref name=\"a\" /> The People's Choice Award was awarded to ''[[Best Boy (film)|Best Boy]]'' by Ira Wohl, which later won Oscar for [[52nd Academy Awards#Awards|Best Documentary Feature]].\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award<ref>[http://tiff.net/thefestival/festivalawards/awardsarchive \"TIFF Awards\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927032100/http://tiff.net/thefestival/festivalawards/awardsarchive |date=2012-09-27 }}. ''tiff.net'', October 14, 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/toronto-film-festival-peoples-choice-award-should-11606670.html|title=Toronto Film Festival People's Choice Award Should Set Pattern for Public Deciding Best Film at Film Festivals|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729052710/http://voices.yahoo.com/toronto-film-festival-peoples-choice-award-should-11606670.html|archive-date=2014-07-29|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n! Film\n! Director\n|-\n| People's Choice Award\n| ''[[Best Boy (film)|Best Boy]]''\n| [[Ira Wohl]]\n|}\n\n==Programme==\n\n===Gala Presentation===\n*''[[The Marriage of Maria Braun]]'' by [[Rainer Werner Fassbinder]]\n*''[[Scum (film)|Scum]]'' by [[Alan Clarke]]\n*''[[The Tempest (1979 film)|The Tempest]]'' by [[Derek Jarman]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiepixfilms.com/festival/4/1979|title=1979 Toronto International Film Festival|accessdate=October 13, 2013}}</ref>\n*''[[Quadrophenia (film)|Quadrophenia]]'' by [[Franc Roddam]]\n*''[[Black Jack (1979 film)|Black Jack]]'' by [[Ken Loach]]\n*''Drugstore Romance'' by [[Paul Vecchiali]]\n*''[[The Onion Field (film)|The Onion Field]]'' by [[Harold Becker]]\n\n===Canadian Cinema===\n*''[[Stone Cold Dead]]'' by [[George Mendeluk]]\n\n===Documentaries===\n*''[[Best Boy (film)|Best Boy]]'' by [[Ira Wohl]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news2/interactives/tiff-peoples-choice-2012/|title=TIFF People's Choice prize heralds film industry kudos|accessdate=October 14, 2013 | work=CBC News}}</ref>\n*''Ett anst\u00e4ndigt liv'' by [[Stefan Jarl]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.tiff.net Official site]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=kCsHKpPd2ssC&pg=PP1&lpg=PP1&dq=TIFF:+A+Reel+History:+1976+-+2012&source=bl&ots=a4476mkVHq&sig=uFGTDJd8TQQqJen8lIHag8t_8f4&hl=en&sa=X&ei=5G1ZUsjcDsvVsgbplICwDw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TIFF%3A%20A%20Reel%20History%3A%201976%20-%202012&f=false TIFF: A Reel History: 1976 - 2012]\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000659/1979 1979 Toronto International Film Festival] at [[IMDb]]\n\n{{TIFF}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Toronto International Film Festival 1979}}\n[[Category:1979 in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Toronto International Film Festival|1979]]\n[[Category:1979 film festivals]]\n[[Category:20th century in Toronto]]\n[[Category:1979 in Canadian cinema]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film festival\n| name           = 1979 Toronto International Film Festival\n| image          = 1979 Toronto International Film Festival poster.jpg\n| caption        = Festival poster\n| host           = Toronto International Film Festival Group\n| number         = \n| opening        = \n| closing        = \n| location       = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]\n| language       = English\n| date           = {{Start date|1979|09|06}}\u2013{{End date|1979|09|15}}\n| website        = {{URL|tiff.net}}\n}}\nThe 4th '''[[Toronto International Film Festival]]''' ('''TIFF''') took place in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada between September 6 and September 15, 1979. This year ''The American Nightmare'' retrospective on [[Horror film|American horror films]] was organized by Canadian critic [[Robin Wood (critic)|Robin Wood]] and Richard Lippe.<ref name=\"a\">{{cite web|url=http://tiff.net/about/tiffhistory|title=TIFF History|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015055839/http://tiff.net/about/tiffhistory|archive-date=2013-10-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Brian De Palma]] and [[George A. Romero]] attended the retrospective as guests.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thetfs.ca/2012/09/04/a-brief-history-of-tiff/|title=A brief history of TIFF|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014145209/http://thetfs.ca/2012/09/04/a-brief-history-of-tiff/|archive-date=October 14, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jam.canoe.ca/Movies/Film_Festivals/Toronto/2009/about/|title=Taking a look back at TIFF|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20131012155556/http://jam.canoe.ca/Movies/Film_Festivals/Toronto/2009/about/|archive-date=2013-10-12|url-status=dead}}</ref> Also this year ''Industry programme trade forum'' was started by festival, which continued till 1991.<ref name=\"a\" /> The People's Choice Award was awarded to ''[[Best Boy (film)|Best Boy]]'' by Ira Wohl, which later won Oscar for [[52nd Academy Awards#Awards|Best Documentary Feature]].\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award<ref>[http://tiff.net/thefestival/festivalawards/awardsarchive \"TIFF Awards\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927032100/http://tiff.net/thefestival/festivalawards/awardsarchive |date=2012-09-27 }}. ''tiff.net'', October 14, 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/toronto-film-festival-peoples-choice-award-should-11606670.html|title=Toronto Film Festival People's Choice Award Should Set Pattern for Public Deciding Best Film at Film Festivals|accessdate=October 14, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729052710/http://voices.yahoo.com/toronto-film-festival-peoples-choice-award-should-11606670.html|archive-date=2014-07-29|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n! Film\n! Director\n|-\n| People's Choice Award\n| ''[[Best Boy (film)|Best Boy]]''\n| [[Ira Wohl]]\n|}\n\n==Programme==\n\n===Gala Presentation===\n*''[[The Marriage of Maria Braun]]'' by [[Rainer Werner Fassbinder]]\n*''[[The Tempest (1979 film)|The Tempest]]'' by [[Derek Jarman]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiepixfilms.com/festival/4/1979|title=1979 Toronto International Film Festival|accessdate=October 13, 2013}}</ref>\n*''[[Quadrophenia (film)|Quadrophenia]]'' by [[Franc Roddam]]\n*''[[Black Jack (1979 film)|Black Jack]]'' by [[Ken Loach]]\n*''Drugstore Romance'' by [[Paul Vecchiali]]\n*''[[The Onion Field (film)|The Onion Field]]'' by [[Harold Becker]]\n\n===Canadian Cinema===\n*''[[Stone Cold Dead]]'' by [[George Mendeluk]]\n\n===Documentaries===\n*''[[Best Boy (film)|Best Boy]]'' by [[Ira Wohl]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news2/interactives/tiff-peoples-choice-2012/|title=TIFF People's Choice prize heralds film industry kudos|accessdate=October 14, 2013 | work=CBC News}}</ref>\n*''Ett anst\u00e4ndigt liv'' by [[Stefan Jarl]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.tiff.net Official site]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=kCsHKpPd2ssC&pg=PP1&lpg=PP1&dq=TIFF:+A+Reel+History:+1976+-+2012&source=bl&ots=a4476mkVHq&sig=uFGTDJd8TQQqJen8lIHag8t_8f4&hl=en&sa=X&ei=5G1ZUsjcDsvVsgbplICwDw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TIFF%3A%20A%20Reel%20History%3A%201976%20-%202012&f=false TIFF: A Reel History: 1976 - 2012]\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000659/1979 1979 Toronto International Film Festival] at [[IMDb]]\n\n{{TIFF}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Toronto International Film Festival 1979}}\n[[Category:1979 in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Toronto International Film Festival|1979]]\n[[Category:1979 film festivals]]\n[[Category:20th century in Toronto]]\n[[Category:1979 in Canadian cinema]]\n", "name_user": "Bartallen2", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding Scum to the 1979 programme.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1979_Toronto_International_Film_Festival"}
{"title_page": "Esan Central", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Esan Central\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            =  \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = [[Local Government Areas of Nigeria|LGA]]\n|motto                  = N'Esan Gha amen!\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_map              =\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            =\n|pushpin_map            =\n|pushpin_label_position =\n|pushpin_mapsize=\n|pushpin_map_caption    =\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       ={{flag|Nigeria}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[States of Nigeria|State]] \n|subdivision_name1      =[[Edo State]]\n|subdivision_type2      = Capital\n|subdivision_name2      =\n|subdivision_type3      = \n|subdivision_name3      = \n|government_footnotes   =\n|government_type        =\n|leader_title           =\n|leader_name            =\n|established_title      =  \n|established_date       = \n|area_magnitude         = \n|unit_pref                = Imperial\n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           =\n|area_land_km2            =\n|population_as_of               = 2006\n|population_footnotes           =\n|population_note                =\n|population_total               =\n|population_density_km2         =\n|timezone               =[[West Africa Time|WAT]]\n|utc_offset             = +1\n|timezone_DST           =\n|utc_offset_DST         = \n|coordinates            = \n|elevation_footnotes    =  \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_ft           = \n|postal_code_type       =  \n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              =\n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''Esan Central Local Government Area''' is a [[Local Government Areas of Nigeria|Local Government Area]] of [[Edo State]], [[Nigeria]]. Its administrative headquarters is in the city of [[Irrua]].\n\nThe [[postal code]] of the area is 310.<ref>{{cite web|title=Post Offices- with map of LGA |publisher=NIPOST |url=http://www.nipost.gov.ng/PostCode.aspx |accessdate=2009-10-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091007011423/http://www.nipost.gov.ng/PostCode.aspx |archivedate=2009-10-07 }}</ref>\n\nIt has an area of 253 km\u00b2 and a population density of 545.1/km\u00b2 <small>[2016]</small><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://citypopulation.de/php/nigeria-admin.php|title=Nigeria: Administrative Division (States and Local Government Areas) - Population Statistics, Charts and Map|website=citypopulation.de|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n\n== Health ==\nIrrua Specialist Teaching Hospital is the only fully functional government owned hospital in the local government area. The hospital is owned by the Federal Government of Nigeria and it is also a teaching hospital for students of the College of Medicine, Ambrose Alli University, Ekpoma.\u21b5\n\nDistribution of hospitals in Esan Central medical zones are Dist. Hospital, Usugbenu and Dist. Hospital, Ewu.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.opendata.edostate.gov.ng/category/dataset/|title=Dataset \u2013 Edo State OpenData|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord missing|Nigeria}}\n{{LGAs and communities of Edo State}}\n\n[[Category:Local Government Areas in Edo State]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Edo State]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Esan Central\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            =  \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = [[Local Government Areas of Nigeria|LGA]]\n|motto                  = N'Esan Gha amen!\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|