nd a population density of 545.1/km\u00b2 <small>[2016]</small><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://citypopulation.de/php/nigeria-admin.php|title=Nigeria: Administrative Division (States and Local Government Areas) - Population Statistics, Charts and Map|website=citypopulation.de|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord missing|Nigeria}}\n{{LGAs and communities of Edo State}}\n\n[[Category:Local Government Areas in Edo State]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Edo State]]\n", "name_user": "Oziomoluabi", "label": "safe", "comment": "Health", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esan_Central"}
{"title_page": "M\u00f3nika Lamperth", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2010}}\n{{Infobox Officeholder \n| name            = M\u00f3nika Lamperth\n| image           = \n| order           = [[Minister of the Interior of Hungary]]\n| term_start      = 27 May 2002\n| term_end        = 9 June 2006\n| predecessor     = [[S\u00e1ndor Pint\u00e9r]]\n| successor       = post abolished\n| order2          = [[Interior Minister of Hungary|Minister of Local Government of Hungary]]\n| term_start2     = 9 June 2006\n| term_end2       = 30 June 2007\n| predecessor2    = post established\n| successor2      = [[Gordon Bajnai]]\n| order3          = [[Government of Hungary|Minister of Social Affairs and Labour of Hungary]]\n| term_start3     = 30 June 2007\n| term_end3       = 5 May 2008\n| president       = \n| predecessor3    = [[P\u00e9ter Kiss]]\n| successor3      = [[Erika Sz\u0171cs]]\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1957|09|05|df=yes}}\n| birth_place     = [[B\u00e1csbokod]], [[Hungary]]\n| profession      = politician, [[jurist]]\n| party           = [[Hungarian Socialist Party]]\n| spouse          = Dr Andr\u00e1s Jegesy\n| children        = Vera <br>Andr\u00e1s\n|}}\n{{eastern name order|Lamperth M\u00f3nika}}\n'''M\u00f3nika Lamperth''' (born 5 September 1957 in [[B\u00e1csbokod]]) is a [[Hungary|Hungarian]] politician and jurist, who served as [[Government of Hungary|Interior Minister]] between 2002 and 2006, after that she became Minister of Local Government until 2007, while [[Ferenc Gyurcs\u00e1ny]] appointed her as [[Government of Hungary|Minister of Social Affairs and Labour]].\n\n==Personal life==\nShe is married to Dr Andr\u00e1s Jegesy. They have a daughter, Vera and a son, Andr\u00e1s.<ref>[http://www.origo.hu/itthon/20030210lamperth.html - Lamperth M\u00f3nika vagyonnyilatkozata - 2003. febru\u00e1r]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20091203035825/http://lamperth.hu/ Official website of 